title: 820-00165  PM_DSW_PWRGD  "chicken or the egg"
message:
I have a 820-00165 that is just sitting there 0.025A  Not enabling 3v3 SUS and turning on the BIOS.

I noticed that PM_DSW_PWRGD is not present at R1451.
This is generated by the SMC.   Isn't this required to enable 3V3_SUS?

Tried forcing it with a 10k and 1k resistor but it gets pulled down.
40 k ohm resistance to ground

title: 820-00165  PM_DSW_PWRGD  "chicken or the egg"
message:
R8141 was high resistance.

You sir are a
[URL='https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/steely-eyed_missile_man#:~:text=steely%2Deyed%20missile%20man%20(plural,problem%20while%20under%20extreme%20pressure.'][SIZE=5][B]steely-eyed missile man[/B][/SIZE][/URL]
 
I have never troubleshot this area.   There was water damage around U7501 however a physical poke and scrape check of R8141 appeared that the resistor was good so I moved on.   Just goes to show you never know!
